The paper proposes a novel grayness index for illumination estimation in color-biased images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which could also place it in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper also mentions processing a 1080p image in ~0.4 seconds, indicating that it involves some form of computational efficiency, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also mentions outperforming state-of-the-art statistical methods and recent deep methods, suggesting that it involves some form of machine learning or statistical analysis, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
